convolutional neural network to label sunspots based on
the McIntosh classification system, aiming to bridge deep
learning with solar astronomy.

One of the earliest methods for capturing sunspots involved projecting the Sun's image
onto paper and tracing it. This simple technique has been used for centuries and is still
relevant for improving solar predictions when satellite data is lacking. However, the number
of sunspot observers has declined, and public awareness of these historical records is low.
I chose to work with sunspot drawings from the Ondřejov and Kanzelhöhe Observatories,
which include details about the observer and weather conditions.
